      "description": "Presenting a meticulously preserved specimen of the FD3S chassis, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This vehicle retains its factory-spec longitudinal front-midship layout, delivering a near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution. The forced induction system operates with seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos, while the 5-speed manual transmission engages with crisp, short-throw precision. Mechanical integrity is paramount; the apex seals maintain optimal compression across all chambers, and the double-wishbone suspension remains taut, free of bushing fatigue. Finished in its original pigment with a flawless interior, this RX-7 represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering, offering an unadulterated analog driving experience with zero deferred maintenance.",
